{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% import "partials/_demo.njk" as ui %}

{% block title %}Buttons · Stisla v3{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <header>
    <h1>Buttons</h1>
    <p class="lead">A clickable control that triggers an action.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Primary</h2>
    <p>
      The main call to action. Use one per surface for the action you most
      want the user to take, like Save, Submit, or Continue.
    </p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">Primary</button>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Secondary</h2>
    <p>
      For actions that sit alongside primary but should not compete with it.
      Common cases are Cancel next to Save, Filter next to Search, or any
      non-prominent control.
    </p>
    <p>
      Two flavors. The filled secondary reads as a peer to primary, useful
      when both actions are equal weight. The outline secondary is quieter
      and sits in the grey ramp, which is the canonical Cancel-next-to-Save
      pairing.
    </p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary">Secondary</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">Outline</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
    <p>The canonical pairing in context.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">Save changes</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">Cancel</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Danger</h2>
    <p>
      For destructive actions like Delete, Remove, or Discard. The filled red
      carries the most weight and is the safe default for a confirm dialog.
      Outline and light are options when a softer treatment fits the surface
      better, like a row-level delete inside a dense table.
    </p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-danger">Danger</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-danger">Outline</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-light-danger">Light</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Tertiary</h2>
    <p>
      An alternative to primary for surfaces where the action should be
      prominent but the brand primary color doesn't fit. Tertiary's color
      flips by theme. Dark in light mode, light in dark mode. Reach for it
      when primary is already taken on the page and a second prominent action
      needs to stand apart.
    </p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-tertiary">Tertiary</button>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Ghost</h2>
    <p>
      No background, no border, just a colored label. Use it for low-stakes
      actions like a modal Close, a Cancel inside a card row, or toolbar
      items. Hover paints a soft tint so the affordance shows up on
      interaction.
    </p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-ghost">Ghost</button>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Other variants</h2>
    <p>
      Stisla v3 ships filled, outline, light, and ghost flavors for every
      Bootstrap theme color. You probably won't need most of these in a real
      app. Reach for primary, secondary, danger, tertiary, or ghost first.
      Everything below is here for the rare case a surface calls for it.
    </p>
    <p>Filled variants for the remaining colors.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-success">Success</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-warning">Warning</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-info">Info</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
    <p>Outline across the remaining colors.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-primary">Primary</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-success">Success</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-warning">Warning</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-info">Info</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
    <p>Light flavors across every color. Soft tinted fill, no border.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-light-primary">Primary</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-light-secondary">Secondary</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-light-success">Success</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-light-warning">Warning</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-light-info">Info</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
    <p>Ghost flavors across every color. No chrome at rest, soft tint on hover.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-ghost-primary">Primary</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-ghost-secondary">Secondary</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-ghost-success">Success</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-ghost-danger">Danger</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-ghost-warning">Warning</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-ghost-info">Info</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Where are <code>btn-light</code> and <code>btn-dark</code>?</h2>
    <p>
      Stisla v3 doesn't restyle BS5's <code>.btn-light</code> or
      <code>.btn-dark</code>. In practice they don't pull their weight as
      semantic categories. <code>.btn-light</code> reads as a barely-visible
      grey button on a white surface, and <code>.btn-dark</code> is
      essentially <code>.btn-primary</code> inverted. BS5's compiled defaults
      still emit, so existing markup keeps working, just unbranded.
    </p>
    <p>
      Use <code>btn-secondary</code> instead. It's mono and inverts per
      theme, which is what <code>.btn-dark</code> (light mode) and
      <code>.btn-light</code> (dark mode) were trying to be. Heads-up on the
      name collision. The light flavors in <em>Other variants</em> above
      (<code>btn-light-primary</code>, <code>btn-light-success</code>, ...)
      are unrelated. Same word, different family. They're per-color soft
      tints, not the BS5 grey button.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Link button</h2>
    <p>No background, no shadow. Underline on hover.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-link">Link button</button>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sizes</h2>
    <p>Heights are pinned across small, default, and large regardless of content.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2 align-items-center">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">Small</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">Default</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Large</button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>With icon</h2>
    <p>
      Any icon component drops into <code>.btn</code> via flexbox
      <code>gap</code>. Icons scale with the button's font size.
    </p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2 align-items-center">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">
        <i data-lucide="plus"></i>
        Leading icon
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">
        Trailing icon
        <i data-lucide="arrow-right"></i>
      </button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Icon only</h2>
    <p>
      Add <code>.btn-icon</code> for a 1:1 square button. Pair with
      <code>aria-label</code> so the action stays announced.
    </p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2 align-items-center">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-icon btn-sm" aria-label="Add">
        <i data-lucide="plus"></i>
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-icon" aria-label="Add">
        <i data-lucide="plus"></i>
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-icon btn-lg" aria-label="Add">
        <i data-lucide="plus"></i>
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-danger btn-icon" aria-label="Delete">
        <i data-lucide="trash-2"></i>
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-icon" aria-label="Edit">
        <i data-lucide="pencil"></i>
      </button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>States</h2>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2 align-items-center">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary active" aria-pressed="true">Active</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" disabled>Disabled button</button>
      <a href="#" role="button" class="btn btn-primary disabled" aria-disabled="true" tabindex="-1">Disabled link</a>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Loading</h2>
    <p>
      Toggle <code>.btn-loading</code> from JS to show a leading spinner. The
      label stays visible. Any leading or trailing icons are hidden so the
      spinner takes their place. Click is blocked while the class is applied.
      Pair with <code>aria-busy="true"</code>.
    </p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2 align-items-center">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-loading btn-sm" aria-busy="true">Saving</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-loading" aria-busy="true">Saving</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-loading btn-lg" aria-busy="true">Saving</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-loading" aria-busy="true">Loading</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-danger btn-icon btn-loading" aria-busy="true" aria-label="Deleting"></button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
    <p>With icons, the spinner replaces them in place.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2 align-items-center">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-loading" aria-busy="true">
        <i data-lucide="plus"></i>
        Adding
      </button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-loading" aria-busy="true">
        Continuing
        <i data-lucide="arrow-right"></i>
      </button>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
    <p>Click to try. The state auto-clears after two seconds.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-demo-loading="2000">
      <i data-lucide="save"></i>
      Save changes
    </button>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Toggle</h2>
    <p>
      <code>data-bs-toggle="button"</code> flips <code>.active</code> and
      <code>aria-pressed</code> on click.
    </p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-bs-toggle="button">Press me</button>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Works on any element</h2>
    <p>
      <code>.btn</code> renders the same on <code>&lt;button&gt;</code>,
      <code>&lt;a&gt;</code>, and form inputs.
    </p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2 align-items-center">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">&lt;button&gt;</button>
      <a href="#" role="button" class="btn btn-primary">&lt;a&gt;</a>
      <input type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" value="<input type=submit>" />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>
{% endblock %}
